story.title: Three Snaps - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: Bree: Thanks for the Snap, Tiff 😉
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Author of THE TALE OF MU, a fantasy novel.

messages.text: Thanks for the Snap, Tiff 😉
What Snap?
The one you just sent us! 😂
I never sent a Snap. My phone was turned off.
Stop playing, Tiff. LOL.
It was definitely you, Tiff. Juuling in the bathroom with Zach.
With a heart-filled, lovey-dovey type of filter. LOL.
I DID NOT take that video.
That’s not me. I swear to God. It can’t be. I’d never use that filter. Yuck.
How could it NOT be you? We both saw it, Tiff. It was you.
I was Juuling in the cafeteria ten minutes ago when it was taken.
Ditching to Juul even on the last day of school! LOL. So Tiff!
I didn’t even do it in the bathroom today.
Well that doesn’t make sense.
It had to be you, Tiff. Nobody but the three of us were on the Snap.
Listen. My phone was OFF until just now. Believe me. It was dead. I needed to charge it!
What?
So you didn’t make out with Zach? I thought he left class to meet up with you?
I wish. I’ve been waiting for that all year.
Where are you now?
Now I really am going to the bathroom lol.
LOL. Take a Snap of you doing dragon’s breath into the toilet bowl LOL.
No way.
Why not? You’ve done it before.
No, it’s not that. Zach’s here.
He wants me to Juul with him in the bathroom 😁
See, I knew you were playing.
No, that means the Snap came true!
Whatever. I’ll tell you how it goes, ladies 😉
Wait. There’s another Snap.
Jessica, where are you right now?!
Jessica?
Heading back from Subway. Got you on speaker in my car. Siri’s voice is so annoying LOL.
What’s the Snap about?
Pull over!
What? Why?
The Snap shows you getting into a car crash!
Come on, Bree LOL.
You’re not going to get me like Tiff did.
It looks real, Jess. I’m not kidding.
And right before you crash the inside of your car has this creepy fire filter and shows you wearing devil horns!
Okay, that’s not funny. You know I’m superstitious.
You run into a bus.
I don’t see any buses. I’m almost back.
Just pull over. Or park and walk back to school. Now! Please!
Okay. Hold on.
Thirty seconds later.
Jessica?
Did you pull over?
Jessica?
Bree! OMG! Jessica just crashed her car!
WHAT?!
I was leaving with Zach to ditch the rest of the day…
And when we got to the parking lot we heard a loud crash.
No!
Was there a bus?
How’d you know? I can’t believe she didn’t see it!
You didn’t see the Snap?
No, I was busy.
Is she okay?
I don’t know. Gigi is calling 9-1-1. She was ditching too. Zach ran over there to see.
I’m coming outside. I don’t care what Mrs. Anderson says.
Check your phone.
Why? There’s nothing.
Do you see Nick?
No. Why would I see Nick?
So you didn’t talk to him or see him or anything?
I texted him during first period. I think he ditched with some of his friends.
You shouldn’t come over here.
Why not? I’m almost through the parking lot.
You didn’t get the Snap?
No, just the ones you and Jessica sent.
I can hear a siren. Is that you way over there?
Bree, stop!
What are you talking about?
Don’t come any closer.
Stop playing with me. I can see you.
Wait. Why are you running away?
Tiff?
Why are you running way over there hiding from me?
Don’t come over here, Bree. I’m serious.
Why not?
The Snap.
What about it?
It shows you killing Nick.
WHAT?! That’s crazy! No way. I’d never do that! I love him.
Then don’t come over here. Go back to Mrs. Anderson’s class or something.
What are you hiding? How’s Jessica? I see an ambulance.
Zach said she’s alive. Looks like she’ll have to go to intensive care.
I got to see her. I got to tell her sorry.
DON’T come over here, Bree. A cop is coming.
It’s my fault she crashed.
If I hadn’t told her about that Snap…
Bree, it’s not your fault. I just saw her Snap, too. Something weird is going on.
Wait. Where are you going?
I think I see Nick. He’s coming from Chandler’s Crossing with his buddies, on the other side of the football field.
Bree!
STOP!
What IS all this?!
Is that a whale?
What are you talking about? Stop running over there!
The sky! It’s purple. There’s a whale swimming. It’s like I’m underwater.
That’s an effect on Snapchat. It’s not real.
What, are those BATS?!
OMG!
They’re attacking me! Where’s Nick? Do you see Nick?
Yeah, I think he sees you. Don’t go over to him, Bree! Stop running!
Where is he? I can’t see him.
There’s fire now. Smoke. The sky is red. Flames. It’s like Jessica’s Snap from inside her car.
But it’s REAL! OMG!
I’m running over. Hold on.
Now the sky is falling. Like the clouds are all black boulders falling on me! OMG, HELP!
What’s that? Do you see that?
Bree, just sit down. Lie on the grass. I’ll be right there.
It’s lava, Tiff! The ground is lava! The DEVIL is coming! I have to do something. I have to fight back. He must be coming for Jessica!
Don’t do anything, Bree! Please.
An angel!
Bree, that’s a cop! Don’t!
He has a magic wand. I can destroy the devil with it.
OMG, Bree! Don’t! Stop! No!
That’s Nick! That’s a gun! Oh, God! No!
It’s fine. It’s not real.
Yes, it is! IT IS REAL!
And you shot him…and now the police have you…
